CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper February 21, 1953, pg. 5, reads: "Discussion Leader... Miss Marjorie Little, of the Religious Education Department of the Kay Boys Club, will lead a timely discussion at Trinity AME Sunday School, corner Francis Street and Wylie Avenue, on Sunday at 9:45 A. M. The intermediates and senior classes will discuss: 'Qualifications Needed for Church Membership.'"
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Marjorie Little wearing dark top with rounded collar and light colored trim around upturned pockets, posed in front of dark curtain in Harris Studio
